Natural Topology Theory:
The Core Equation k∗
= n∗
A Complete Proof via Topological Invariant Convergence
February 2026
Abstract
We introduce Natural Topology Theory (NTT), a unied framework in which
divergence serves as the driving force of convergence rather than an obstacle to be
removed. The central object is a density function ρ(k) ∝kd threading three struc-
tural layers: a meta-renormalization group, a quantum gravity zone, and a topolog-
ical invariant oor. The fractal dimension dis shown to be uniquely self-determined
by the triple convergence of homology, homotopy, and cobordism (Theorem 1). The
energy scale kis shown to inhabit the intersection R+ ∩L2(X)∩H1(X) (Theorem 2).
From these foundations, we derive the core equation
k∗
= n∗
,
establishing a one-to-one correspondence between energy scale extrema and dimen-
sion number extrema. As corollaries, we obtain dimension quantization and the
necessity of 3+1-dimensional spacetime.
